# üîß Cloudflare Workers Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to configure secrets for your deployment environments
#
# WARNING: Never commit this file with actual secrets!
# Use this as a template to know what variables to set via:
# - wrangler secret put for Cloudflare Workers
# - GitHub repository secrets for CI/CD

# ==========================================
# üóÑÔ∏è Database Configuration (Choose One)
# ==========================================

# Option A: Traditional Database
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://user:password@host:5432/database
# DATABASE_URL=sqlite+aiosqlite:///./app.db

# Option B: Cloudflare D1 Database (Recommended)
# For Workers Binding Mode (Production):
# DATABASE_URL=d1+binding://DB

# For HTTP Client Mode (Development/Testing):
# DATABASE_URL=d1+aiosqlite://DATABASE_ID?account_id=ACCOUNT_ID&api_token=API_TOKEN

# D1 HTTP Mode Credentials (Optional - for development/testing)
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=your-account-id
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your-api-token
# D1_DATABASE_ID=your-database-id

# ==========================================
# üîÑ Redis Configuration
# ==========================================

# Redis connection string
# REDIS_URL=redis://host:6379/0
# REDIS_PASSWORD=your-redis-password-or-upstash-token

# ==========================================
# üîê Supabase Authentication
# ==========================================

# Supabase project configuration
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anonymous-key
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ==========================================
# üîí Security Configuration
# ==========================================

# JWT and encryption keys
# JWT_SECRET_KEY=your-jwt-secret-key
# ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-encryption-key

# ==========================================
# üìä Monitoring & Observability (Optional)
# ==========================================

# Sentry error tracking
# SENTRY_DSN=your-sentry-dsn
# SENTRY_CLIENT_DSN=your-client-sentry-dsn

# ==========================================
# üìù Setup Instructions
# ==========================================

# 1. Cloudflare Workers Secrets:
#    Use: ./scripts/set-secrets.sh [environment]
#    Or manually: echo "value" | wrangler secret put SECRET_NAME --env [environment]

# 2. GitHub Actions Secrets:
#    Use: ./scripts/set-secrets-github.sh [environment]
#    Or manually via GitHub web interface or GitHub CLI

# 3. D1 Database Setup (if using D1):
#    - Create databases: wrangler d1 create faster-app-[env]
#    - Update wrangler.toml with database IDs
#    - Apply migrations: wrangler d1 migrations apply faster-app-[env]

# 4. Local Development:
#    - Copy this file to .env.local (gitignored)
#    - Set actual values for local testing
#    - Use D1 HTTP mode for local D1 testing

# ==========================================
# üåç Environment-Specific Notes
# ==========================================

# Development:
# - Use smaller resource limits
# - Enable debug logging
# - Use test/development credentials

# Staging:
# - Mirror production setup
# - Use staging-specific resources
# - Test with staging data

# Production:
# - Use production credentials
# - Enable performance optimizations
# - Configure monitoring and alerting